Summaries for UGT2B10 Gene

GeneCards Summary for UGT2B10 Gene

UGT2B10 (UDP Glucuronosyltransferase Family 2 Member B10) is a Protein Coding gene. Among its related pathways are Porphyrin and chlorophyll metabolism and Metabolism of xenobiotics by cytochrome P450. GO annotations related to this gene include carbohydrate binding and glucuronosyltransferase activity. An important paralog of this gene is UGT2B15.

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot for UGT2B10 Gene

  • UDB10_HUMAN,P36537

  • UDPGT is of major importance in the conjugation and subsequent elimination of potentially toxic xenobiotics and endogenous compounds.
